==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
The origin of the name is not known for sure, but it is old, predating the Spanish, and is thought to derive from the Nahuatl [[Xicuahua]], or "dry, sandy place".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/tʃɪˈwɑwɑ/}}

===Noun===
{{en-proper-noun}}

# A [[desert]] [[state]] in northwestern [[Mexico]].
# The [[capital city]] of the Mexican state of Chihuahua.

====Related terms====
*[[chihuahua]]
*[[Chihuahuan Desert]]

